{
  "doc_id": "14125",
  "text": "Antimicrobial drug resistance (AMR) is a well-recognized global problem and high rates of resistance to first-line antibiotics among Gram-negative bacteria have been reported in Uganda [CITATION_1] . As such, routine surveillance studies are necessary to monitor antibiotic resistance trends in low-income countries where antibiotic selection pressure is likely to be high.",
